{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"eq70ln13eqi7r5dpy11otvf","title":"Hot Reload","desc":"","updated":1681659387385,"created":1676213478943,"custom":{},"fname":"computing.web.hot-reload","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"docs"},"contentHash":"f7e1d41ded42fe376c8389669c10c203","links":[],"anchors":{"hot-reload":{"type":"header","text":"Hot reload","value":"hot-reload","line":8,"column":0,"depth":1},"tools":{"type":"header","text":"Tools","value":"tools","line":12,"column":0,"depth":2},"live-server":{"type":"header","text":"live-server","value":"live-server","line":14,"column":0,"depth":3},"nodemon":{"type":"header","text":"nodemon","value":"nodemon","line":22,"column":0,"depth":3},"node-dev":{"type":"header","text":"node-dev","value":"node-dev","line":32,"column":0,"depth":3},"ts-node-dev":{"type":"header","text":"ts-node-dev","value":"ts-node-dev","line":42,"column":0,"depth":3},"tsc":{"type":"header","text":"tsc","value":"tsc","line":54,"column":0,"depth":3},"webpack":{"type":"header","text":"webpack","value":"webpack","line":60,"column":0,"depth":3}},"children":[],"parent":"2uv1yc4tj8j2w18porl9kbw","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"hot-reload\">Hot Reload<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#hot-reload\"></a></h1>\n<h1 id=\"hot-reload-1\">Hot reload<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#hot-reload-1\"></a></h1>\n<p>Hot reload consist at reloading without rebuilding a code resource, usually code.</p>\n<h2 id=\"tools\">Tools<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#tools\"></a></h2>\n<h3 id=\"live-server\">live-server<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#live-server\"></a></h3>\n<p>It can reload JS, HTML and CSS.</p>\n<p>Url: <a href=\"https://github.com/tapio/live-server\">https://github.com/tapio/live-server</a></p>\n<p>Review: not tested</p>\n<h3 id=\"nodemon\">nodemon<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#nodemon\"></a></h3>\n<p>Restart a NodeJS application when files are changed.</p>\n<p>It watches a directory.</p>\n<p>Url: <a href=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/nodemon\">https://www.npmjs.com/package/nodemon</a></p>\n<p>Review: not tested</p>\n<h3 id=\"node-dev\">node-dev<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#node-dev\"></a></h3>\n<p>Restart a NodeJS application when files are changed.</p>\n<p>It watches the require calls, it do not restart if an unused file is changed.</p>\n<p>Urm: <a href=\"https://github.com/fgnass/node-dev\">https://github.com/fgnass/node-dev</a></p>\n<p>Review: not tested</p>\n<h3 id=\"ts-node-dev\">ts-node-dev<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#ts-node-dev\"></a></h3>\n<p>Optimization of node-dev</p>\n<p>It uses <a href=\"https://github.com/TypeStrong/ts-node\">ts-node</a>, a JIT typescript.</p>\n<p>It do not recompile everything when a used script file is changed.</p>\n<p>Url: <a href=\"https://github.com/wclr/ts-node-dev\">https://github.com/wclr/ts-node-dev</a></p>\n<p>Review: not tested</p>\n<h3 id=\"tsc\">tsc<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#tsc\"></a></h3>\n<p>This is the official Typescript command.</p>\n<p>To do a watch, the command is \"tsc --watch\".</p>\n<h3 id=\"webpack\">webpack<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#webpack\"></a></h3>\n<p>You can use:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>the command \"webpack --watch\"</li>\n<li>webpack-dev-server</li>\n</ul>\n<p>There is a typescript plugin as well.</p>","noteIndex":{"id":"os9ivsua46f0vj4p0yyqhx0","title":"Root","desc":"","updated":1681658547293,"created":1676142715220,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"docs"},"contentHash":"f2b2cb51b9be244f6389288b0e9baa6c","links":[],"anchors":{"awesome-knowledge":{"type":"header","text":"Awesome Knowledge","value":"awesome-knowledge","line":7,"column":0,"depth":1